svg.text: * = lifeSigns are sent very seldom to keep the overhead low
* = 1.1 represents createOutputGather, 1.2-1.102 represents calculateOffsetVolume activities, 100 OffsetClasses
The scheduler fills in its internal schedule according to some not further defined scheme
If we use a jobFinishedAck message, we can piggybag the next job
jobFinished(1.2, token=[MemoryToken(OffsetClass,ro), MemoryToken(OffsetVolume, local to node!)])
* = 1.103 represents a 'store' Operation, those are available after the first calculate, the OffsetVolume-MemoryToken has to be taken into account!
The previous steps are repeated until no more activities can be executed and all activities are finished
